The Nigerian military on Thursday said as part of the Boko Haram/Islamic State of West Africa elements campaign of terror and destruction, the terrorists on Tuesday attacked troops’ location in Kukawa town in Borno State. Coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Major General John Enenche, in a statement on Thursday said the attack by the terrorists was a deliberate attempt to reverse the milestone achievements recorded regarding IDPs in the area. Major General John Enenche See Also






